.TH CWE-863 7 "2025-12-11" "CWE Top 25 (2025)" "Software Weakness Reference"
.SH NAME
CWE\-863 \- Incorrect Authorization
.SH RANK
2025 CWE Top 25 rank: \fB#17\fR (2024 rank: 18).
.SH CLASSIFICATION
Class: Access Control.
.SH DESCRIPTION
An authorization check exists but is logically flawed, so it permits actions it should deny: comparing the wrong field, only checking authentication, or failing open. Unlike Missing Authorization, the check is present but wrong.
.SH MITIGATION
Check the specific permission for the specific object the actor touches, not merely that they are authenticated. Fail closed on any error. Centralise the policy so the same correct check is reused.
.SH KNOWN EXPLOITED VULNERABILITIES
CISA KEV catalog (as of 2026-06-15): \fB16\fR exploited CVEs mapped to this weakness.
.PP
CVE\-2019\-7192, CVE\-2021\-3560, CVE\-2021\-22986, CVE\-2021\-30533, CVE\-2021\-40655, CVE\-2022\-41091, CVE\-2023\-21715, CVE\-2023\-22518, CVE\-2023\-24880, CVE\-2023\-38035, CVE\-2024\-21287, CVE\-2024\-38856, CVE\-2025\-21479, CVE\-2025\-21480, CVE\-2025\-24200, CVE\-2025\-55177.
.SH EXAMPLES
One vulnerable\->fixed pair per ecosystem (Node.js, Python, Java, Go, PHP).
.SS Node.js
\fIVulnerable:\fR
.RS
.EX
app.get('/orders/:id', requireAuth, async (req, res) => {
  const order = await Order.findById(req.params.id);
  res.json(order);   // any logged-in user can read any order
});
.EE
.RE
\fIFixed:\fR
.RS
.EX
app.get('/orders/:id', requireAuth, async (req, res) => {
  const order = await Order.findById(req.params.id);
  if (!order || order.userId !== req.user.id) return res.sendStatus(403);
  res.json(order);   // object-level ownership check
});
.EE
.RE
.SS Python
\fIVulnerable:\fR
.RS
.EX
@app.get('/orders/<int:oid>')
def view(oid):
    order = Order.get(oid)
    if current_user.is_authenticated:   # only checks login, not ownership
        return order.json()
    abort(401)
.EE
.RE
\fIFixed:\fR
.RS
.EX
@app.get('/orders/<int:oid>')
def view(oid):
    order = Order.get(oid)
    if order is None or order.owner_id != current_user.id:
        abort(403)                      # object-level ownership check
    return order.json()
.EE
.RE
.SS Java
\fIVulnerable:\fR
.RS
.EX
@GetMapping("/orders/{id}")
public Order view(@PathVariable Long id, Authentication auth) {
    if (auth.isAuthenticated())         // login only, not ownership
        return repo.findById(id).orElseThrow();
    throw new AccessDeniedException("401");
}
.EE
.RE
\fIFixed:\fR
.RS
.EX
@GetMapping("/orders/{id}")
public Order view(@PathVariable Long id, @AuthenticationPrincipal User me) {
    Order o = repo.findById(id).orElseThrow();
    if (!o.getOwnerId().equals(me.getId()))
        throw new AccessDeniedException("403");   // ownership check
    return o;
}
.EE
.RE
